        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 28 at 2:33AM MDT until July 28 at 5:45AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is
expected.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Montana, including the following
county, Valley.

* WHEN...Until 545 AM MDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is
likely.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 232 AM MDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause small stream flooding.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Glasgow, Tampico, Hinsdale, Vandalia, The Bentonite Plant and
Whatley.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
